{meta: title A Courtroom Then Goodbye}
{meta: artist Patsy Cline}
{meta: composer Eddie Miller and W.S. Stevenson}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]The first scene was the church then the [D7]altar
Where we claimed each other with tears of joy we [G]cried
Our friends wished us luck there [C]forever
As we [D7]walked from the church side by [G]side
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
The next scene was a crowded [D7]courtroom
And like strangers we sat side by [G]side
Then I heard the judge make his [C]decision
And no [D7]longer were we man and [G]wife
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
I hate the sight of that [D7]courtroom
Where man made laws push God's laws [G]aside
Then the clerk wrote our story in the [C]record
A Church A [D7]Courtroom And Then [G]Goodbye
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
We walked from that courtroom [D7]together
We shook hands and once again we [G]cried
Then it was the end of our [C]story
A Church A [D7]Courtroom And Then [G]Goodbye
{end_of_verse}
